{"nodes":[{"pos":[12,49],"content":"Compiler Error C3772 | Microsoft Docs","needQuote":false,"needEscape":true,"nodes":[{"content":"Compiler Error C3772 | Microsoft Docs","pos":[0,37]}]},{"content":"Compiler Error C3772","pos":[619,639]},{"content":"\"name\" : invalid friend template declaration","pos":[640,684]},{"content":"It is invalid to declare a friend of a class template specialization.","pos":[690,759]},{"content":"You cannot declare an explicit or partial specialization of a class template and in the same statement declare a friend of that specialization.","pos":[760,903]},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>name<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> placeholder identifies the invalid declaration.","pos":[904,962],"source":" The *name* placeholder identifies the invalid declaration."},{"content":"To correct this error","pos":[972,993]},{"content":"Do not declare a friend of a class template specialization.","pos":[1003,1062]},{"content":"If appropriate for your application, declare a friend of the class template, or declare a friend of a particular partial or explicit specialization.","pos":[1072,1220]},{"content":"Example","pos":[1229,1236]},{"content":"The following code example fails because it declares a friend of a partial specialization of a class template.","pos":[1240,1350]},{"content":"See Also","pos":[2193,2201]},{"content":"Templates","pos":[2205,2214]},{"content":"Template Specialization","pos":[2248,2271]}],"content":"---\ntitle: \"Compiler Error C3772 | Microsoft Docs\"\nms.custom: \"\"\nms.date: \"11/04/2016\"\nms.reviewer: \"\"\nms.suite: \"\"\nms.technology: \n  - \"devlang-csharp\"\nms.tgt_pltfrm: \"\"\nms.topic: \"article\"\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"C3772\"\ndev_langs: \n  - \"C++\"\nhelpviewer_keywords: \n  - \"C3772\"\nms.assetid: 63e938d4-088d-41cc-a562-5881a05b5710\ncaps.latest.revision: 13\nauthor: \"corob-msft\"\nms.author: \"corob\"\nmanager: \"ghogen\"\ntranslation.priority.ht: \n  - \"de-de\"\n  - \"es-es\"\n  - \"fr-fr\"\n  - \"it-it\"\n  - \"ja-jp\"\n  - \"ko-kr\"\n  - \"ru-ru\"\n  - \"zh-cn\"\n  - \"zh-tw\"\ntranslation.priority.mt: \n  - \"cs-cz\"\n  - \"pl-pl\"\n  - \"pt-br\"\n  - \"tr-tr\"\n---\n# Compiler Error C3772\n\"name\" : invalid friend template declaration  \n  \nIt is invalid to declare a friend of a class template specialization. You cannot declare an explicit or partial specialization of a class template and in the same statement declare a friend of that specialization. The *name* placeholder identifies the invalid declaration.  \n  \n### To correct this error  \n  \n-   Do not declare a friend of a class template specialization.  \n  \n-   If appropriate for your application, declare a friend of the class template, or declare a friend of a particular partial or explicit specialization.  \n  \n## Example  \n The following code example fails because it declares a friend of a partial specialization of a class template.  \n  \n```cpp  \n// c3772.cpp  \n// compile with: /c  \n  \n// A class template.  \n    template<class T> class A {};  \n  \n// A partial specialization of the class template.  \n    template<class T> class A<T*> {};  \n  \n// An explicit specialization.  \n    template<> class A<char>;  \n  \nclass X {  \n// Invalid declaration of a friend of a partial specialization.  \n    template<class T> friend class A<T*>; // C3772  \n  \n// Instead, if it is appropriate for your application, declare a   \n// friend of the class template. Consequently, all specializations   \n// of the class template are friends:  \n//    template<class T> friend class A;  \n// Or declare a friend of a particular partial specialization:  \n//    friend class A<int*>;  \n// Or declare a friend of a particular explicit specialization:  \n//    friend class A<char>;  \n};  \n```  \n  \n## See Also  \n[Templates](../../cpp/templates-cpp.md)   \n[Template Specialization](../../cpp/template-specialization-cpp.md)   \n"}